WM. F. ENGELBERTH v. MARY ENGELBERTH. [No. 20,

April Term, 1930.]

Decided May 21st, 1930. The cause was argued before Bond, C. J., Pattison, Urner, Adkins, Offutt, Digges, Parke, and Sloan, JJ. H. Courtenay Jenifer, with whom were Jenifer & Jenifer on the brief, for the appellant. Allan W. Rhynhart, with whom was William P. Cole, Jr., on the brief, for the appellee. Adkins, L,

delivered the opinion of the Court.
